  "prompt": "Which is the best laptop under 40000 INR?",
  "response": "As of the latest information, there are several good laptop options available in India for under 40,000 INR. These laptops generally offer a balance between performance and affordability. Here are some options you might consider:\n\n1. **HP 15s**: \n   - Processor: AMD Ryzen 3 or Intel Core i3 (depending on the variant).\n   - RAM: 8GB\n   - Storage: 256GB SSD or 1TB HDD\n   - Display: 15.6-inch Full HD\n   - Features: Good for multitasking and general use.\n\n2. **Acer Aspire 5**: \n   - Processor: AMD Ryzen 3 3200U or Intel Core i3\n   - RAM: 4GB/8GB (upgradable)\n   - Storage: 256GB SSD or 1TB HDD\n   - Display: 15.6-inch Full HD\n   - Features: Known for decent build quality and performance.\n\n3. **Lenovo IdeaPad S145**: \n   - Processor: Intel Core i3 10th Gen\n   - RAM: 4GB/8GB (upgradable)\n   - Storage: 1TB HDD\n   - Display: 15.6-inch Full HD\n   - Features: Offers a good build and usability for daily tasks.\n\n4. **ASUS VivoBook 15**:\n   - Processor: Intel Core i3 or AMD Ryzen 3\n   - RAM: 4GB/8GB (upgradable)\n   - Storage: 256GB SSD or 1TB HDD\n   - Display: 15.6-inch Full HD\n   - Features: Slim design and lightweight, suitable for students and professionals.\n\n5. **Dell Inspiron 15 3000**:\n   - Processor: Intel Core i3 10th Gen\n   - RAM: 4GB/8GB (upgradable)\n   - Storage: 1TB HDD\n   - Display: 15.6-inch HD/Full HD\n   - Features: Reliable brand with good customer support.\n\nWhen choosing a laptop, it\u2019s important to consider what you need it for. If you need more storage, opt for a 1TB HDD model. If you want faster performance, consider one with an SSD. Also, ensure that the RAM is adequate for your tasks, especially if you plan on running multiple applications simultaneously or using it for tasks beyond basic browsing and document editing. It\u2019s always a good idea to check the latest models and reviews to ensure you\u2019re getting the best value for your budget.",
